17/06/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- EU spokeswoman Sheena Thompson said Wednesday (16 June) that the international community is hopeful that Macedonia's ruling coalition parties will reach a compromise on the power decentralisation law package. Decentralisation is the last challenge to full implementation of the Ohrid Peace Accord.
In other news, the Social Democratic Alliance for Macedonia and the Liberal Democratic Party launched talks Wednesday on renewing their coalition agreement. The two parties joined forces four years ago. (Makfax, A1 TV - 17/06/04)
